Agreement] SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is made as of March 14, 2014 (the “Agreement Date”) by and among RE COLUMBIA, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Columbia” or “Owner”), RE COLUMBIA TWO LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Columbia Two”), RE CAMELOT LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Camelot”), RE YAKIMA LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Yakima”), and RE CLEARWATER LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Clearwater”). Camelot, Columbia Two, Yakima, and Clearwater are collectively referred to herein as the “Project Companies” and individually as a “Project Company”. The Project Companies and Columbia are collectively referred to herein as the “Parties” and individually as a “Party.” The terms “Project Company” and “Party” shall include the permitted successors and permitted assignees of such Person. Certain capitalized terms used in this Agreement are given defined meanings in Appendix A attached hereto. RECITALS A. Camelot holds or anticipates holding certain real property option, leasehold, right-of-way and/or fee interests in all or a portion of that certain land located in Kern County, California (the “Camelot Property”), on which it intends to develop a 45 MWAC solar energy generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (the “Camelot Project”). The Camelot Property is described on the attached Exhibit A-1. B. Columbia Two holds or anticipates holding certain real property option, leasehold, right-of-way and/or fee interests in all or a portion of that certain land located in Kern County, California (the “Columbia Two Property”), on which it intends to develop a 15 MWAC solar energy generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (the “Columbia Two Project”). The Columbia Two Property is described on the attached Exhibit A-2. C. Yakima holds or anticipates holding certain real property option, leasehold, right-of-way and/or fee interests in all or a portion of that certain land located in Kern County, California (the “Yakima Property”), on which it intends to develop a 20 MWAC solar energy generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (the “Yakima Project”). The Yakima Property is described on the attached Exhibit A-3. D. Clearwater holds or anticipates holding certain real property option, leasehold, right-of-way and/or fee interests in all or a portion of that certain land located in Kern County, California (the “Clearwater Property”), on which it intends to develop a 20 MWAC solar energy generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (the “Clearwater Project”). The Clearwater Property is described on the attached Exhibit A-4. The Camelot Project, the Columbia Two Project, the Yakima Project and the Clearwater Project are individually referred to herein as a “Project,” and collectively as the “Projects.” The Camelot Property, the Columbia Two Property, the Yakima Property and the Clearwater Property are individually referred to herein as a “Property” and collectively referred to herein as the “Properties.” E. The Project Companies own all of the membership interests in Columbia in proportion to the nominal capacity rating of their respective Projects. 2 #4819-9501-3656 F. The Parties are parties to the Interconnection Agreement pursuant to which the Projects will be interconnected to the distribution system owned and operated by SCE. The Parties are also parties to the Co-Tenancy Agreement pursuant to which the Parties will share in certain rights, responsibilities and costs and in which Columbia acts as manager for the Project Companies. G. Columbia holds or anticipates holding certain real property options, franchise, leasehold, right-of-way, encroachment rights, crossing rights, non-disturbance agreements, waivers, consents and/or fee interests (the “Shared Premises Property Rights”) described in Exhibit B for the Shared Premises. H. Certain of the Interconnection Customer Interconnection Facilities under the Interconnection Agreement, including the Gen-Tie Line Assets, will be jointly used by all of the Project Companies (such facilities, the “Shared Facilities”), as more particularly described in Exhibit D. A description of the location of the Gen-Tie Line on the Shared Premises is included in Exhibit C. I. Columbia will (i) develop, design and construct and (ii) operate, maintain, repair, replace, and decommission (collectively, “Operation and Maintenance”) the Shared Facilities for the exclusive benefit, operation and use of the Projects in accordance with this Agreement and the Interconnection Agreement. J. The Parties desire to provide in this Agreement for: (i) the sharing of the use of such Shared Facilities necessary or convenient to each Project Company’s ownership, development and operation of its respective Project; and (ii) sharing of the costs incurred pursuant to the Shared Premises Property Rights and the development, design, construction and Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities. NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged by the Parties, the Parties agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 SHARED PREMISES 1.1 Declaration of Intention. Owner shall own or otherwise hold the Shared Premises Property Rights and the Shared Facilities, but shall exercise such rights for the exclusive benefit of the Project Companies. Owner shall hold and use the Shared Premised Property Rights and the Shared Facilities solely for purposes of performing the Shared Facilities Services. The arrangements contemplated by this Agreement are not being made with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making or sharing in any profits from the ownership of Columbia, the use of the Shared Premises Property Rights or the operation and use of the Shared Facilities, but are instead intended as a form of binding agreement whereby the Project Companies can accomplish their respective objectives of requiring that Owner perform the Shared Facilities Services in connection with their respective Projects and businesses and to 3 #4819-9501-3656 enable the Project Companies to perform and discharge certain of their obligations under the Interconnection Agreement and their respective Power Purchase Agreements. 1.2 Shared Premises Property Rights. (a) The Shared Premises Property Rights as of the Agreement Date are described on Exhibit B. The Shared Premises Property Rights allow or will allow for the development, design, construction, Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities. (b) Owner shall exercise its rights as owner of the Shared Premises Property Rights for the benefit of, and to perform the Shared Facilities Services on behalf of each Project Company in accordance with such Project Company’s Proportionate Share. Each Project Company hereby consents to the performance of the Shared Facilities Services by Owner on the terms and subject to the conditions of this Agreement, on behalf of each other Project Company. To the extent the Shared Premises Property Rights as of the Agreement Date do not include all property rights necessary for development, construction, Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities, and such additional rights must be acquired from any fee owner, lessee, a licensees or easement holder of any of the Properties, to the extent that any Project Companies have the right to do so, such Project Companies shall grant or convey, or cause to be granted or conveyed, any such property rights to Columbia as are necessary to allow the development, construction, Operation and Maintenance of such Shared Facilities as are described in such Exhibits, as the same may be amended from time to time. Any such property rights hereafter acquired for use as Shared Premises Property Rights (including pursuant to Section 1.7 hereof with respect to any Additional Premises Rights)) shall be conveyed AS IS and without warranty, and all rights conveyed or granted to Columbia pursuant to the immediately preceding sentence shall be conveyed AS IS and without warranty, SPECIFICALLY INCLUDING WITHOUT WARRANTY OF TITLE, EITHER EXPRESSED OR IMPLIED, AND ANY WARRANTIES ARISING BY COMMON LAW OR STATUTE, EXCEPT AS TO PERSONS CLAIMING UNDER OR THROUGH THE GRANTOR OF SUCH RIGHT. Upon the grant, conveyance and contribution of such additional required easements rights pursuant to this Section 1.2(b), such rights shall be included in the definition of Shared Premises Property Rights, and the Parties shall prepare amendments to the applicable exhibits and the Memorandum to reflect the addition of such additional required rights or interests to the Shared Premises Property Rights. Any acquisition of additional Shared Premises Property Rights shall not have any material adverse effect on the rights of the Parties hereunder or under their respective Power Purchase Agreement. (c) Each Party’s Proportionate Share as of the Agreement Date is more particularly described in Exhibit E attached hereto, which Exhibit shall be updated and approved by the Parties from time-to-time in accordance with this Agreement. 1.3 Maintenance of the Shared Premises. Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities shall be the responsibility of Owner as provided in Article 5 below. Costs and expenses incurred by Owner to maintain or comply with the Shared Premises Property Rights shall be shared by the Project Companies in accordance with Article 3 below. 1.4 Continuance of Shared Premises Property Rights. Owner shall take, to the extent it can do so, all actions necessary to continue the Shared Premises Property Rights (including the 4 #4819-9501-3656 Franchise Agreement) in full force and effect, and the Project Companies will cooperate with and assist Owner in so doing. No Party shall violate, or take, fail to take or permit any action that could reasonably be expected to violate or result in the loss of, any of the Shared Premises Property Rights regarding such rights. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, and except as qualified herein, no Project Company shall communicate directly with the grantor of the Shared Premises Property Rights regarding those rights. Columbia shall be the sole Party authorized to communicate directly with the grantor of the Shared Premises Property Rights; provided, however, that Columbia shall not contact or communicate with the grantor of the Shared Premises Property Rights on any material matter without first consulting with all of the Project Companies affected by such Shared Property Premises Rights. Any amounts due under the terms of the Shared Premises Shared Premises Property Rights shall be paid by Owner, subject to reimbursement from the Project Companies in accordance with Article 3 below. Notwithstanding the forgoing, except as hereinafter provided, nothing herein shall prevent or prohibit a Project Company from communicating directly with a grantor of a Shared Premises Property Right if such communication is necessary for such Project Company to develop, operate, maintain, repair, replace or decommission its Project but does not affect the Shared Premises Property Rights, particularly if such grantor is a counterparty to a separate agreement with such Project Company relative to its Project. 1.5 Entry on to the Shared Premises. (a) By Project Companies. Subject to the additional rights described below, each Project Company shall have the right to enter onto the Shared Premises to the extent reasonably necessary for the following limited purposes: (i) inspection of such Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities located thereon, (ii) development, design, construction, or Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities on such Shared Premises to the extent Owner defaults in its obligation to perform such activities, subject to Article 10 below, or (iii) repair of the Shared Facilities in the event of an Emergency and the failure or unavailability of Owner or its representatives to respond timely to such Emergency. Except in the event of an Emergency, a Project Company shall give Owner and the other Project Companies, or other persons identified to the Project Companies in writing to receive such notice on behalf of Owner, at least 48-hours prior notice of its intent to enter upon the Shared Premises for the foregoing purposes (said notice may be by telephone, e-mail, or any other recognized electronic means in addition to any other methods of notice authorized herein). In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required, but the Project Company shall give notice of entry onto the Shared Premises to Owner as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter. Any Project Company entering on the Shared Premises shall follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by Owner or its contractors, if applicable, with respect to the Shared Premises or otherwise applicable to the relevant Shared Premises under any Shared Premises Property Rights documentation burdening such Shared Premises and which has been made available to all of the Project Companies. Notwithstanding the above, if any part of the Shared Premises is also subject to a lease agreement, easement, license or other similar agreement with a Project Company for its respective Project, the Project Company may enter upon any part of the Shared Premises that is also part of such Project Company’s rights pursuant to any such lease agreement, easement, license or other similar agreement without the need to give prior notice or obtain consent as provided in this Section 1.5(a) unless such entry is with respect to the Shared Facilities located thereon. As owner of the Shared Facilities, Owner shall have access to the Shared Facilities at 5 #4819-9501-3656 any time and for any lawful purpose that is consistent with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. (b) Secured Party. A Secured Party of a Project Company shall have the right to enter onto the Shared Premises for the purposes described in Section 1.5(a)(i). 1.6 No Interference. The performance by Owner of the Shared Facilities Services on behalf of any Project Company shall not be permitted to unreasonably interfere with the use and enjoyment by any other Project Company of its rights arising under this Agreement, except as provided in this Agreement. 1.7 Additional Premises Rights. To the extent that any additional premises (the “Additional Premises”) or rights therein (other than the Shared Premises and Shared Premises Property Rights) that relate to the Shared Facilities or operation thereof are required by any Project Company, or that are needed or would materially benefit, in the reasonable belief of Owner, the interconnection or operation of the Projects consistent with the Interconnection Agreement or Co-Tenancy Agreement, such Project Company or the Owner, as the case may be, shall give written notice to the other Parties of such requirement, with a reasonable explanation why such Additional Premises or rights therein are needed. Each Party receiving such notice shall have thirty (30) days after receiving such notice to determine if such Additional Premises or rights therein are also needed for its Project and to so notify the other Parties in writing of its election to participate or not to participate in such Additional Premises Rights. Failure to notify the other Parties of its election to participate shall be deemed an election not to participate. Any Additional Premises or rights therein needed by only one of the Project Companies may be acquired and held in the name of such Project Company and shall not be Shared Premises under this Agreement. Any Additional Premises or rights therein that the Parties agree are needed by more than one Project Company shall be (i) procured by such Project Companies and conveyed to the Owner, (ii) added as Shared Premises and shall become Shared Premises Property Rights hereunder, and (iii) used in accordance with each Project Company’s Proportionate Share; provided, however, that to the extent that not all of the Project Companies elect to participate in such Additional Premises rights, each Project Company’s Proportionate Share with respect to such Additional Premises only shall be determined on the basis of the relative interests of the Project Companies that have elected to participate in such Additional Premises. In the event that Owner reasonably believes that the Additional Premises are needed or would materially benefit a Project Company that has elected not to participate therein and that such Project Company should participate therein, Owner may submit the matter to dispute resolution under Article 13. The costs of acquiring such Additional Premises rights shall be borne by the participating Parties in proportion to their respective Proportionate Shares. Upon acquisition of any Additional Premises or rights therein pursuant to this Section 1.7, Owner shall prepare amendments to Exhibits B, C and D and the Memorandum to reflect the addition of the Additional Premises, which shall be submitted to each Project Company for its review and approval. Notwithstanding anything in this Section 1.7 to the contrary, no Additional Premises or rights therein shall be acquired if such acquisition would cause of violation of any existing Shared Premises Property Rights, a breach of the Interconnection Agreement, the Co-Tenancy Agreement, any Power Purchase Agreement or any Security Documents; provided, however, that if requested by Owner, a Project Company will use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain any necessary consents 6 #4819-9501-3656 under Security Documents related to its Project or otherwise allow the other participating Project Companies to proceed with the acquisition of the Additional Premises. 1.8 Covenants Running with the Land. The beneficial rights created by this Agreement and the covenants of the Parties made in this Agreement shall be deemed to be covenants running with and binding upon the land pursuant to applicable law for the duration of the term of this Agreement and shall bind and benefit all current and future owners of the lands bound and benefited by this Agreement but only for the term of this Agreement, including the Shared Premises, Shared Premises Property Rights, the Additional Premises and the Properties. 1.9 Maintenance Expenses. The Parties intend that all costs, expenses and obligations pursuant to the Shared Premises Property Rights after the Agreement Date, including without limitation, any taxes, rents, franchise fees, maintenance and upkeep costs shall be deemed an Shared O&M Expense regardless of whether such amounts are included in the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget pursuant to Section 3.5. ARTICLE 2 SHARED USE AND SHARED FACILITIES 2.1 Construction of and Interests in Shared Facilities. (a) Construction of Shared Facilities. Owner shall, or shall cause a contractor to, develop, design, engineer and construct the Shared Facilities and any Additional Facilities which will become Shared Facilities pursuant to Section 2.3, in accordance with this Agreement, the Interconnection Agreement and the Co-Tenancy Agreement. A depiction and description of each of the Shared Facilities as of the date hereof is attached hereto as Exhibits C and D, respectively (collectively, the “Shared Facilities Exhibits”). The Shared Facilities Exhibits shall be updated and amended by the Parties from time-to-time in accordance with this Agreement. The Parties acknowledge that the Shared Facilities will be constructed pursuant to the EPC Contract. Owner shall not change any of the design, plans or specifications in the EPC Contract as of the Agreement Date if such change, either individually or in the aggregate with all other changes since the Agreement Date, would result in an increase in the contract price under the EPC Contract of more than ten percent (10%) or adjust the project schedule under the EPC Contract such that Substantial Completion of the initial Shared Facilities will occur later than December 31, 2014, unless (i) it has first submitted any such changes, including all necessary drawings and supporting documentation and information, to the Project Companies for review and approval and (ii) such changes are approved by a Supermajority in Interest of the Project Companies; provided, that if a Project Company fails to approve or disapprove such changes within five (5) Business Days after receipt of all necessary drawings and supporting documentation and information, such changes shall be deemed approved. If an increase in the EPC Contract or an adjustment in the project schedule is approved by a Supermajority of the Project Companies pursuant to this subsection (a) Owner shall not, without the approval of a Supermajority of the Project Companies using the process described above, make any further changes in the in the design, plans or specifications in the EPC Contract, if such change, either individually or in the aggregate with all other changes since the date of the approval of the revised EPC Contract Price, would result in an increase in the contract price under the EPC 7 #4819-9501-3656 Contract of more than ten percent (10%) over such previously approved revised EPC Contract price. Similarly, if an adjustment in the project schedule under the EPC Contract is approved by Supermajority of the Project Companies, Owner shall not make any further adjustment in the project schedule without the approval of a Supermajority of the Project Companies. (b) Effect of Dispute on Construction. In no event shall any Dispute regarding changes in the EPC Contract or an Other Construction Contract require Owner to delay or suspend construction, it being agreed between the Parties that an adequate remedy exists at law and waives any right to seek an injunction to delay or suspend such construction. Owner may delay or suspend construction if full funding of construction is not provided by the Project Companies. (c) Coordination. In the event the Project Companies are engaged in construction activities on their respective Properties at the time the Shared Facilities or other Owner construction projects are underway, the Owner and the Project Companies shall reasonably coordinate their construction activities to minimize disruption to their respective construction schedules and to ensure continued access in and to the Parties’ Properties and continued rights to use the Shared Facilities. (d) Monitoring and Step-In Rights. The Project Companies shall have the right, each at its sole cost and expense, to monitor the construction of the Shared Facilities and Additional Facilities by Owner, and Owner shall afford reasonable access to the Project Companies. Any Project Company exercising such monitoring right shall not interfere with the construction activities of Owner or its contractors and shall comply with all of Owner’s and its contractors’ workplace safety and security requirements. If (i) construction of the Shared Facilities under the EPC Contract ceases for a period of twenty (20) consecutive days or more for reasons other than due to force majeure, default by EPC Contractor, failure of a Project Company to pay amounts due under this Agreement or Governmental Authority directive, and any Project Company delivers notice thereof to Owner, and (ii) construction of the Shared facilities is not re-started within ten (10) days following such written notice, then the Project Company with the greatest Proportionate Share may, without any obligation to do so, step in and replace Owner as manager of the work under the EPC Contract or Other Construction Contract, as applicable. That Project Company shall give each of the other Parties written notice of whether or not it will step in and replace Owner within five (5) days after the expiration of such ten (10) day notice period, and failure to provide such notice within such five (5) day period shall be deemed an election not to step in and replace Owner. If the Project Company with the greatest Proportionate Share declines or is deemed to have declined to step in, then the Project Company with the next largest Proportionate Share may elect to step in and so on until a Project Company elects to step in; provided that in each case, such Project Company shall give each of the other Parties written notice of whether or not it will step in and replace Owner within five (5) days after the expiration of the previous Project Company’s election or deemed election not to step in, and failure to provide such notice within such five (5) day period shall be deemed an election not to step in and replace Owner. If no Project Company elects to exercise its step in rights, the Owner shall continue in its role as manager of the EPC Contract. Following the exercise of such step-in rights, all provisions of this Agreement applicable to Owner with respect to installation and construction of such Shared Facilities or Additional Facilities shall apply to the Project Company replacing Owner’s role as manager of construction, including the right to 8 #4819-9501-3656 use and enjoy all Shared Premises Property Rights and other property rights held by Owner. In the event step-in rights are exercised as provided under this subsection 2.1(d), Owner shall provide all assistance and cooperation as reasonably required to complete the Shared Facilities or Additional Facilities, including without limitation assignment to the applicable Project Company of the EPC Contract or Other Construction Contracts and other contracts and agreements to which Owner is a party in connection with the installation and construction of the Shared Facilities or Additional Facilities, (“Project Contracts”), as the same are necessary or convenient to such Project Company for purposes of completing the Shared Facilities or Additional Facilities to the extent permitted by the terms of such Project Contracts. Owner shall use commercially reasonable efforts to cause such step-in rights to be included in the Project Contracts for purposes of recognition by the counterparties to the Project Contracts of the Project Companies’ step-in rights hereunder. (e) Payment of Shared Facilities Construction Costs. Owner shall be initially responsible for all costs incurred for design, installation and construction of the Shared Facilities, including the costs of Additional Facilities that subsequently become Shared Facilities (the “Shared Facilities Construction Costs”) except as otherwise provided herein. Each Project Company shall pay its Proportionate Share of the Shared Facilities Construction Costs to the bank account designated by Owner within five (5) Business Days of receipt of any invoice for such costs by Owner. Such invoice shall specify each Project Company’s Proportionate Share of the Shared Facilities Construction Costs in reasonable detail, including a list and description of the amounts incurred which are subject to reimbursement. If a Project Company disputes the invoiced amount, it shall nonetheless pay the disputed amount, and shall refer the Dispute for resolution in accordance with provisions of Article 13. Any disputed amount that if finally determined by dispute resolution pursuant to Article 13 or by mutual agreement to have been improperly invoiced shall be promptly refunded to the Project Company through an assessment to the Project Companies in accordance with their Proportionate Shares of the refund amount, taking into account amounts already paid by each of the Project Companies, such that, after such assessments have been paid, each of the Project Companies will have paid its Proportionate Share of all costs determined by dispute resolution to be Shared Facilities Construction Costs. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in no event shall any dispute regarding allocation of costs require Owner to delay or suspend construction of any Shared Facilities. In the event Owner receives any reimbursement from any third party of Shared Facilities Construction Costs (or of costs for construction of any Additional Facilities (as defined in Section 2.3 below) which have been paid by the Project Companies, Owner shall promptly remit to the Project Companies their respective shares of such reimbursement in proportion to the share of such costs paid by such Project Companies. If an additional Person becomes a party to this Agreement (a “New Party”), such New Party shall pay its Proportionate Share of the Shared Facilities Construction Costs to Owner. If such costs have already been paid by the Project Companies, the New Party shall instead pay such amount to the Project Companies in proportion to their respective Proportionate Shares. (f) Financial Security. On the Agreement Date, each Project Company shall deliver to Owner a Letter of Credit for the full estimated cost of such Project Company’s share of the Shared Facilities Construction Cost as set forth in the EPC Contract as of the Agreement Date, as security for such Project Company’s obligation to reimburse Owner for such Project Company’s Proportionate Share of the Shared Facilities Construction Costs pursuant to 9 #4819-9501-3656 Section 2.1(e); provided, however, that face amount of such Letters of Credit will be reduced as each Project Company makes payments under Section 2.1(d) concurrently with and in the amount of such payments. If a Project Company fails to pay amounts due in accordance with Section 2.1(e), Owner shall have a right to draw on the Letter of Credit for amount due from the Project Company.
